1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE JOINT
RESOLUTION 1047 By: Jenkins
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
to refer to the people for their approval or
8 rejection a proposed amendment to Section 21 of
Article V of the Constitution of the State of
9 Oklahoma; eliminating Board on Legislative
Compensation; setting legislator salaries based on
10 certain date; providing exception; providing
procedures for referral of question to voters;
11 prescribing certain General Elections for voting;
providing ballot title; and directing filing.
12
13
14 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
15 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
16 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
17 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
18 the following proposed amendment to Section 21 of Article V of the
19 Constitution of the State of Oklahoma to read as follows:
20 Section 21. A. The Legislature shall enact laws to prohibit
21 members of the Legislature from engaging in activities or having
22 interests which conflict with the proper discharge of their duties
23 and responsibilities.
24
Req. No. 15520 Page 1

1 B. The Board on Legislative Compensation is hereby created.
2 Said Board shall be composed of five members appointed by the
3 Governor, two members appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the
4 Senate, and two members appointed by the Speaker of the House of
5 Representatives. The members appointed by the Governor shall be
6 from religious organizations, communications media, nonstate-
7 supported educational institutions, labor organizations, and retail
8 business; the members appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the
9 Senate shall be from agricultural and civic organizations; and the
10 members appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives
11 shall be from manufacturing and from professional fields not
12 otherwise specified. No member of the Legislature may be appointed
13 to or serve on the Board. In addition to the members above provided
14 for, the Chairman of the Oklahoma Tax Commission and the Director of
15 State Finance shall serve as ex officio nonvoting members of said
16 Board. The Chairman of said Board shall be designated by the
17 Governor. Members of the Legislature shall receive such
18 compensation as shall be fixed by the Board on Legislative
19 Compensation. If a member of the Legislature is incarcerated due to
20 being charged with a criminal offense and subsequently is found
21 guilty of the offense or pleads guilty or nolo contendere to the
22 offense, the legislator shall return to the state any compensation
23 the legislator received from the state while the legislator was
24 incarcerated prior to the guilty verdict or plea or nolo contendere
Req. No. 15520 Page 2

1 plea and shall not receive any compensation from the state during
2 any incarceration following such verdict or plea. Said Board shall
3 each two years review the compensation paid to the members of the
4 Legislature and shall be empowered to change such compensation; such
5 change to become effective on the fifteenth day following the
6 succeeding general election. The members of the Board shall serve
7 without compensation, but shall be entitled to receive necessary
8 travel and subsistence expense as provided by law for other state
9 officers.
10 SECTION 2. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
11 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
12 the following proposed amendment to the Constitution of the State of
13 Oklahoma by adding a new Section 21A to Article V thereof, to read
14 as follows:
15 A. Except as otherwise provided by this section, compensation
16 for legislators shall be fixed at the amount in effect as of
17 November 1, 2025.
18 B. The Legislature may submit a question for modifications to
19 the salary amounts for legislators to a vote of the people to occur
20 in the year of a General Election which also occurs during the year
21 of the election for the office of President of the United States.
22 C. The question shall be submitted using either a Joint
23 Resolution or a bill, but the measure shall not be presented to the
24 Governor for action.
Req. No. 15520 Page 3

1 D. If a majority of the people approve the proposal at the
2 applicable General Election, the salary of legislators shall remain
3 in effect until any further modification to such salary amount in
4 the manner prescribed by this section.
5 E. The methods prescribed by this section shall be exclusive
6 and the salary of legislators shall not be modified using any other
7 procedure.
8 SECTION 3. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
9 amendment as set forth in SECTIONS 1 and 2 of this resolution shall
10 be in the following form:
11 BALLOT TITLE
12 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
13 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
14 This measure amends the Oklahoma Constitution. It amends Section
15 21 of Article 5 and it would create a new Section 21A of Article
16 5. It would eliminate the Board on Legislative Compensation.
17 Salaries for legislators would be fixed at the amount in effect
18 as of November 1, 2025, unless modified using a new process. In
19 any year in which the General Election is also the year of the
20 Presidential Election, the Legislature could submit a question
21 to modify the salary of legislators to a vote of the people.
22 The proposal could be contained in either a joint resolution or
23 a bill, but it would not be sent to the Governor. Instead the
24 measure would always be a state question. If a majority of
Req. No. 15520 Page 4

1 voters approve the modification, the salary amount would be in
2 effect until any other changes were made. All changes to
3 legislator salaries would have to be approved using this method.
4 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
5 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
6 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
7 SECTION 4. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
8 immediately after the passage of this resolution, shall prepare and
9 file one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in
10 SECTION 3 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the
11 Attorney General.
